Q(inspection): Have you given your landlord reasonable access to your apartment to inspect it and make repairs?  
A:Yes
	Q(otherz):GOTO:heat
A:No
	Q(bad):You have to this is the law. Your landlord must have your permission to enter your apartment. Housing courts generally require landlords to give tenants at least 24 hours’ notice before entering. The notice may be less if there is an emergency, like a water leak. Please come again if the problem was not fixed.







